09/06/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have arrested three Albanians for alleged drug trafficking, media reported on Monday (June 8th), including a police officer working at the Tirana International Airport.
This is the second case in a month in which an Albanian official was detained in Turkey on drug-related charges.
In May, Turkish police arrested Agim Haxhiu, second secretary at the Albanian Embassy in Skopje, who allegedly used a diplomatic car to travel from Macedonia to Turkey carrying 65kg of heroin.
(Top Channel, News 24, Top News, Vizion +, Ora News - 08/06/09)
